23/11/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Free trade between Albania and Romania is to begin in January, according to local press reports Friday (21 November). During his visit to Bucharest earlier in the week, Prime Minister Fatos Nano discussed economic co-operation between the two countries. A trade agreement was signed earlier this year as part of the Memorandum on Trade Liberalisation sealed by Albania, Macedonia, Bulgaria, Croatia, Romania, Serbia-Montenegro and Bosnia and Herzegovina. Albania has already signed free trade agreements with all memorandum countries as well as Kosovo. Discussions are under way with Turkey. (Albanian Daily News - 21/11/03)
